headline: This Blue-Chip Dividend Stock Just Raised Its Payout by 7%. Should You Buy Shares Here?
summary: J.P. Morgan’s recent 7.1% dividend increase to $1.50 per share, backed by record earnings and a new $50 billion share buyback plan, highlights strong capital management and signals confidence in sustained shareholder returns despite sector headwinds.
